cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DC, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the decentralization and reward system of a blockchain-based social media platform, which falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and social and behavioral sciences (cs.SOC). The use of Delegated Proof-of-Stake (DPoS) consensus protocol and cryptocurrency transfers also relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
